President Obama released a statement expressing his gratitude for Danielle Gray, who has been a valuable member of his team for the past ten years. He praised her legal expertise, policy knowledge, sense of humor, decency, and understanding of the American people's hopes and challenges. Gray played a significant role in shaping policies related to the economy, job creation, veterans' opportunities, and the confirmation of two Supreme Court justices. As Cabinet Secretary and close advisor, she ensured that government agencies focused on providing equal opportunities for hardworking Americans and promoting the administration's values. Although Gray is departing, the President will continue to seek her counsel, and he believes she will continue to contribute to the pursuit of justice in the legal system and the country.